STEPS TAKEN
I created tmp directory in Linux directory using the command, mkdir
I created xfusioncorp.sh file using the touch command
I used the ls –la command to view the contents of the created file and view its permission
I used sudo chmod 555 /tmp/xfusioncorp.sh to give read and execute permission to myself, , group and others
I used ls -la /tmp/xfusioncorp.sh to confirm and view the read and execute permission given to myself, group and others 
I used the command, git status to Identify Untracked Files <files that exist in my folder but haven't been added to Git yet> ,view Staged Changes <files that I have already run git add on and are now ready to be committed> , view Unstaged Changes < shows me if I have modified files since my last commit but haven't "added" them yet> ,  view Branch Information< the branch I am currently on> , Check Sync Status <If my local work is "ahead" of what is on GitHub, meaning I have committed changes that still need to be pushed>
I ran git add Day4 command to stage Day4 file
I used git commit -m “details” to commit Day4 files
I used the command, git push to push the files to my remote repo on github
I used the command git status to confirm if the files were successfully pushed to my github

